 so doing, she shows how color television disrupted and reframed the very idea of television while it simultaneously revealed the tensions about technology's relationship to consumerism, human sight, and the natural world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Television / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311069633240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478093664?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478093664zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478093664/original  a978-3-11-069633-2 Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA